---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
    <div class="img">
        <picture>
            <source media="(min-width: 1200px)" 
                    srcset="/images/detail/desktop/image-manage-hero.jpg,
                            /images/detail/desktop/image-manage-hero@2x.jpg 2x" />

            <source media="(min-width: 500px)" 
                    srcset="/images/detail/tablet/image-manage-hero.jpg 689w,
                            /images/detail/tablet/image-manage-hero@2x.jpg 1378w" />

            <source srcset="/images/detail/mobile/image-manage-hero.jpg 311w,
                            /images/detail/mobile/image-manage-hero@2x.jpg 622w" />

            <img src="/images/detail/desktop/image-manage-hero.jpg" alt="">
        </picture>
    </div>

    <div class="project-grid">
        <div>
            <div class="description">
                <h1 class="description__title">Manage</h1>
                <p class="description__body">This project required me to build a fully responsive landing page to the designs provided. I used HTML5, along with CSS Grid and JavaScript for the areas that required interactivity, such as the testimonial slider.</p>
                <p class="description__tag">Interaction Design / Front End Development</p>
                <p class="description__tag">HTML / CSS / JS</p>
                <button class="button__secondary">
                    <span class="button__text">View Project</span>
                </button>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div>
            <h2>Project Background</h2>
            <p>
                This project was a front-end  challenge from Frontend Mentor. It’s a platform that 
                enables you to practice building websites to a design and project brief. Each challenge 
                includes mobile and desktop designs to show how the website should look at different 
                screen sizes. Creating these projects has helped me refine my workflow and solve 
                real-world coding problems. I’ve learned something new with each project, helping 
                me to improve and adapt my style.
            </p>

            <h2>Static Previews</h2>
            <div class="img">
                <picture>
                    <source media="(min-width: 1200px)"
                            srcset="/images/detail/desktop/image-manage-preview-1.jpg 635w,
                                    /images/detail/desktop/image-manage-preview-1@2x.jpg 1270w" 
                            sizes="44vw" />

                    <source media="(min-width: 500px)"
                            srcset="/images/detail/tablet/image-manage-preview-1.jpg 689w,
                                    /images/detail/tablet/image-manage-preview-1@2x.jpg 1378w" />

                    <source srcset="/images/detail/mobile/image-manage-preview-1.jpg 313w,
                                    /images/detail/mobile/image-manage-preview-1@2x.jpg 626w" />

                    <img src="/images/detail/desktop/image-manage-preview-1.jpg" alt="">
                </picture>
            </div>
            <div class="img">
                <picture>
                    <source media="(min-width: 1200px)"
                            srcset="/images/detail/desktop/image-manage-preview-2.jpg 635w,
                                    /images/detail/desktop/image-manage-preview-2@2x.jpg 1270w"
                            sizes="44vw" />

                    <source media="(min-width: 500px)"
                            srcset="/images/detail/tablet/image-manage-preview-2.jpg 689w,
                                    /images/detail/tablet/image-manage-preview-2@2x.jpg 1378w" />

                    <source srcset="/images/detail/mobile/image-manage-preview-2.jpg 313w,
                                    /images/detail/mobile/image-manage-preview-2@2x.jpg 626w" />
                    <img src="/images/detail/desktop/image-manage-preview-2.jpg" alt="">
                </picture>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>
</Layout>